## 1. What was run

Three fixtures × 200 log₂-spaced grid points × two algebraically-equivalent routes each, with multiple per-record observables recorded so the analysis can avoid committing to a single observable definition prematurely:

| Fixture | Route A | Route B | Sweep parameter |
|---|---|---|---|
| Schwarzschild horizon approach | `f_A = 1.0 − (2.0/r)` | `f_B = (r − 2.0)/r` | `r − 2 ∈ [2⁻⁴⁰, 2⁻²]` |
| SR Lorentz argument | `f_A = 1.0 − (β·β)` | `f_B = (1.0 − β)·(1.0 + β)` | `1 − β ∈ [2⁻⁴⁰, 2⁻²]` |
| Conical / small-angle | `f_A = 1.0 − cos(θ)` | `f_B = 2.0·sin(θ/2)²` | `θ ∈ [2⁻⁴⁰, 2⁻²]` |

Per record: `f_A, f_B, u_A, u_B, u_div, j_A_own_ulp, j_B_own_ulp, j_div, off_lattice_residual_in_ulps, divergence_float, cross_binade_flag`.

