## 8. What is *not* claimed

- ✗ No claim that G-1 is a real candidate. The graduation gate is not met.
- ✗ No claim that the joint `(j_A, j_B)` distribution is geometric content rather than conditioning content. The C-confound is unresolved.
- ✗ No claim that the fixture-distinguishable fingerprints carry information beyond what a C-only model would predict. Phase 2 will inform this.
- ✗ No verdict. This is characterization. The candidate stays in Phase 1 indefinitely until the mechanism is fully stated (criterion 4 graduation), or until characterization argues it should be dropped.

